TMUX CHEATSHEET                     q to close
Leader: Ctrl-b

PANES
 %       Split vertical
 "       Split horizontal
 z       Zoom/unzoom pane
 x       Close pane
 o       Next pane
 q       Show pane numbers
 { }     Swap pane left / right
 !       Break pane out to its own window
 :join-pane -s <win>  Pull pane in from another window

SESSIONS
 a       New session
 s       Browse & switch sessions
 ( )     Previous / next session
 L       Toggle last session
 $       Rename session
 k       Kill current session
 d       Detach session

WINDOWS
 c       New window
 ,       Rename window
 n / p   Next / previous window
 0-9     Switch to window by number
 w       Browse & switch windows

SCROLL / COPY MODE  (enter: [ , exit: q)
 h j k l    Move
 v          Start selection
 V          Select line
 y          Copy selection
 ]          Paste (outside scroll mode: Leader ])
 /          Search forward
 ?          Search backward

OTHER
 b       Toggle status bar
 [       Enter scroll/copy mode

EDITING  (emacs/readline — works in most shell prompts)
 Ctrl-a     Start of line
 Ctrl-e     End of line
 Ctrl-u     Kill to start of line
 Ctrl-k     Kill to end of line
 Ctrl-w     Kill word back
 Alt-b      Word back
 Alt-f      Word forward
 Alt-d      Kill word forward
 Ctrl-y     Yank last kill
